● The Case for My Candidacy

I see the problem.
I've already started solving it.

This isn't a pitch about potential. It's a record of action — and a plan to scale it with Google's support.

⚠ The Problem I See
📵
Digital tools are invisible in classrooms
Most students at my university have never used Google Workspace beyond basic search. Powerful tools like Colab, Forms, and Looker Studio remain unknown.
🏚️
The urban-rural literacy gap is widening
Elementary students in Medan's surrounding areas receive zero technology exposure. The disparity compounds each year without intervention.
🤖
AI anxiety is replacing AI opportunity
Students fear AI will replace them instead of seeing it as a tool to amplify their capabilities. No one is teaching them the difference.
✦ What I've Already Done
🏘️
Built a 300-member learning community
Grew and moderated an online Discord community from zero — creating a self-sustaining space for knowledge exchange and peer mentorship.
✏️
Directly mentored 60+ students
As Teaching Assistant and private tutor, I've supported 40+ university students and 20 elementary students — in both Math and English.
🛠️
Shipped 5 real products for real users
From a transit navigation app using Google Maps API to an AI study companion — all built to solve actual problems students face daily.

● If selected as GSA

My first 12 months
as your GSA.

This isn't a wishlist. These are three programs I've already planned — with a real audience, a real campus, and a real community of 300+ people ready to participate. I just need the Google network to scale them.

01
Google Workspace Bootcamp
A 4-week intensive bootcamp introducing Docs, Sheets, Slides, Meet, and Forms to 100+ incoming freshmen — with real academic project use cases, not toy exercises.
Target: 100 freshmen · 4 weeks · Semester 1
02
AI Literacy for Non-Tech Majors
Monthly workshops demystifying Gemini, Colab, and AI-assisted research for students in Education, Social, and Humanities — the majority who are left out of the AI conversation.
Target: 80 students/month · Cross-faculty
03
Digital Literacy Outreach
Taking Google tools to elementary schools in Medan's surrounding areas — the same gap I've been filling as a private tutor. Structured, measurable, repeatable program built on my existing classroom experience.
Target: 3 schools · 150 students · Year 1
● The Person Behind the Work
Grace Fachrina Rajagukguk

Frontend Dev Community Lead EdTech Math Tutor

I became a developer
because teaching wasn't enough.

I started as a math tutor — and I was good at it. But every session I ran into the same wall: students who grasped concepts in class but couldn't find resources, tools, or community to keep going at home.

So I started building. First a Discord community. Then web apps. Then AI tools. Each project was my answer to a problem I watched real students struggle with. Not portfolio pieces — field experiments.

Becoming a Google Student Ambassador is the natural next step: access to Google's ecosystem, tools, and network to take what I've built in my corner of Medan and make it available to everyone.
